    {
      "id": "8Z9Fjd_PavMVZFjd_CQBt",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1514.5176840094105,
      "y": 1651.010664588093,
      "width": 780.29931640625,
      "height": 800,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1503560288,
      "version": 996,
      "versionNonce": 234771040,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771520663404,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "load balancer sits in front of RESTful API\n& stateful, bi directional websocket servers\n=> distributes traffic across those servers \n\nRestful api\n- cluster of stateless HTTP servers that handle req/res traffic\n- handles auxiliary tasks i.e. adding/removing friends, updating user profiles etc.\n\nwebsocket servers\n- handle real time update of friend's locations\n- each client 1 persistent ws conn with server\n- loc update -> then its updated via this conn\n\nRedis\n- stores most recent locatio ndata for each active user\n- TTL set on each entry in the cache\n- when TTL expires, user is no longer active\n    - entry gets deleted\n- every update refreshes the TTL\n*other KV stores that \n\nUser DB\n- store user data\n- user friendship data\n- SQL/ NoSQL can be used\n\nlocation history DB\n - users' historical loc data\n\nredis pub/ sub server\n- GBs of MEM can hold millions of channels\n- (in this design) user's own chann",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "load balancer sits in front of RESTful API\n& stateful, bi directional websocket servers\n=> distributes traffic across those servers \n\nRestful api\n- cluster of stateless HTTP servers that handle req/res traffic\n- handles auxiliary tasks i.e. adding/removing friends, updating user profiles etc.\n\nwebsocket servers\n- handle real time update of friend's locations\n- each client 1 persistent ws conn with server\n- loc update -> then its updated via this conn\n\nRedis\n- stores most recent locatio ndata for each active user\n- TTL set on each entry in the cache\n- when TTL expires, user is no longer active\n    - entry gets deleted\n- every update refreshes the TTL\n*other KV stores that \n\nUser DB\n- store user data\n- user friendship data\n- SQL/ NoSQL can be used\n\nlocation history DB\n - users' historical loc data\n\nredis pub/ sub server\n- GBs of MEM can hold millions of channels\n- (in this design) user's own chann",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
