    },
    {
      "id": "XgK0z5wYIycdmF_MG5qw4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2015.3218845981432,
      "y": 2767.6506434148314,
      "width": 1112.13916015625,
      "height": 175,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b32",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1203695200,
      "version": 30,
      "versionNonce": 823076768,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771521130295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "i.e.\n1. bob publishes loc update to the BE via websocket\n2. ws server then publishes to his own channel\n3. i (alice) has an active friend Bob, have my websocket server being subscribed to bob's channel.\n4. the websocket server then receives this new update via redis push\n5. websocket handler function gets invoked, and for each active friend, function recomputes the distance\n6. if new distance is within the search radius, the new loc & timestamp are sent via the websocket connect to me",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "i.e.\n1. bob publishes loc update to the BE via websocket\n2. ws server then publishes to his own channel\n3. i (alice) has an active friend Bob, have my websocket server being subscribed to bob's channel.\n4. the websocket server then receives this new update via redis push\n5. websocket handler function gets invoked, and for each active friend, function recomputes the distance\n6. if new distance is within the search radius, the new loc & timestamp are sent via the websocket connect to me",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fv9TxEKm4tYKYIaf08EFZ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 155.05759300269824,
      "y": 3120.17968132957,
      "width": 1466.89892578125,
      "height": 375,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b33",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1961777056,
      "version": 1322,
      "versionNonce": 1599773280,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771553252340,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Periodic location update\n1. client sends loc update to LB\n2. LB forwards loc update to persistent WS conn on the WS server for the client\n3. WS server saves loc data in location history DB (3)\n4. WS server updates new loc in the location cache. this refreshses the TTL (4)\n    WS server also saves the new location in a vairiable in the user's WS conn handler for subsequent distance calcs (with friedns)\n5. WS server publishes new loc to the user's channel in the redis pub/sub server (5)\n* steps 3-5 can be exec-ed in parallel\n6. when redis pub/sub receive loc update on a channel, it broadcasts update to all subscribers (WS connection handlers)\nin this case, the subscribers are the online friedns of the user sending the udpate\nfor each subscriber, its WS conn handler will receive the user loc update\n7. the WS servers that these handlers lives, then computes the distance between the user sending update & the loc data stored in this local variable\n8. if distnace within radius, new location & last updated timestamp are sent to subscriber's client, else update is dropped\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Periodic location update\n1. client sends loc update to LB\n2. LB forwards loc update to persistent WS conn on the WS server for the client\n3. WS server saves loc data in location history DB (3)\n4. WS server updates new loc in the location cache. this refreshses the TTL (4)\n    WS server also saves the new location in a vairiable in the user's WS conn handler for subsequent distance calcs (with friedns)\n5. WS server publishes new loc to the user's channel in the redis pub/sub server (5)\n* steps 3-5 can be exec-ed in parallel\n6. when redis pub/sub receive loc update on a channel, it broadcasts update to all subscribers (WS connection handlers)\nin this case, the subscribers are the online friedns of the user sending the udpate\nfor each subscriber, its WS conn handler will receive the user loc update\n7. the WS servers that these handlers lives, then computes the distance between the user sending update & the loc data stored in this local variable\n8. if distnace within radius, new location & last updated timestamp are sent to subscriber's client, else update is dropped\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
