      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b35",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1997219744,
      "version": 271,
      "versionNonce": 796521056,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771552823295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "computation is repeated for every subscriber to the channel\ni.e. 400 friends on average, assume 10% is online & nearby == 40\n40 locations updates ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "computation is repeated for every subscriber to the channel\ni.e. 400 friends on average, assume 10% is online & nearby == 40\n40 locations updates ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "si01vX69FCBvPZ_DxI2fJ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 146.80779849671114,
      "y": 3710.263457894634,
      "width": 621.279541015625,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b36",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 277043104,
      "version": 456,
      "versionNonce": 1682744928,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771552823295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "API design\n\nperiodic location update\nsend (lat, lng, timestamp) -> NIL\n\nclient receives loc udpates\ndata receive (lat, lng, timestamp)\n\nwebsocket init\nclient send (lat, lng, timestamp) -> List[(lat, lng, timestamp), ...]\n\nsubscribe to new friend\nsend (friendId) -> (lat, lng, timestamp)\n\nubsubscribe a friend\nsend (friendId) -> nil\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "API design\n\nperiodic location update\nsend (lat, lng, timestamp) -> NIL\n\nclient receives loc udpates\ndata receive (lat, lng, timestamp)\n\nwebsocket init\nclient send (lat, lng, timestamp) -> List[(lat, lng, timestamp), ...]\n\nsubscribe to new friend\nsend (friendId) -> (lat, lng, timestamp)\n\nubsubscribe a friend\nsend (friendId) -> nil\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "utdfdqoB_U7R97UAhd11K",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 875.1200956101027,
      "y": 3710.381215198853,
      "width": 862.6993408203125,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b37",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1844663904,
      "version": 620,
      "versionNonce": 1420352096,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771552823295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "DATA model\n\nuser (friend)\nlocation\n\nlocation cache - latest locs of all active users who have had nearby friends featured on\nkey: user_id\nvalue: {lat, lng, timestamp}\n\nlocation history DB - store historical loc\n{user_id, lat, lng, timestamp}\n- need a DB that handle heavy write well\n- can horizontally scale => NoSQL\n- can shard by userId\n- this sharding scheme ensures that load is evenly distributed among all the shards\n    & operationally it is ez to maintain\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "DATA model\n\nuser (friend)\nlocation\n\nlocation cache - latest locs of all active users who have had nearby friends featured on\nkey: user_id\nvalue: {lat, lng, timestamp}\n\nlocation history DB - store historical loc\n{user_id, lat, lng, timestamp}\n- need a DB that handle heavy write well\n- can horizontally scale => NoSQL\n- can shard by userId\n- this sharding scheme ensures that load is evenly distributed among all the shards\n    & operationally it is ez to maintain\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "pDq6XPUTFX4w-rzgP9OB7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1825.5774296850086,
      "y": 3704.9340543572443,
      "width": 922.0195922851562,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b38",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 203293280,
      "version": 901,
      "versionNonce": 1398705760,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "id": "PtWWKZVmw_T_BGi3pCOxC",
          "type": "arrow"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1771552823295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "why not use DB?\n\n1. auto purge + ez update\n- \"nearby friends\" feature only care about current loc\n- only need to store 1 loc per user\n- redis is excellent choice => else u need to keep updating\n- also supports TTL, allowing us to auto purge users from the cache who are no longer active\n\n2. durability:\n- curr locations do not need to be durably stored\n- if redis instance goes down, easily replace with new instance\n    & let the cache get filled as new loc updates stream in\n- active users can miss loc udpates form friends for an update cycle or 2\n(acceptable tradeoff) => can further discuss",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "why not use DB?\n\n1. auto purge + ez update\n- \"nearby friends\" feature only care about current loc\n- only need to store 1 loc per user\n- redis is excellent choice => else u need to keep updating\n- also supports TTL, allowing us to auto purge users from the cache who are no longer active\n\n2. durability:\n- curr locations do not need to be durably stored\n- if redis instance goes down, easily replace with new instance\n    & let the cache get filled as new loc updates stream in\n- active users can miss loc udpates form friends for an update cycle or 2\n(acceptable tradeoff) => can further discuss",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
